parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, loss of coolant, and engine failure, leading to a potential fire hazard and loss of vehicle control.
Turbo failure can cause loss of power, engine stalling, and engine failure, leading to a potential loss of vehicle control and accidents.
Engine failure can cause loss of power, engine stalling, and engine failure, leading to a potential loss of vehicle control and accidents.

Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Other issues, such as lubrication delivery system design flaws, can cause engine failure, loss of power, and accidents.
